{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf3c19dbc-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s134"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"134"},"text":"§ 134.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appeal to the Patent Trial and Appeal Board","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idf3c19dbd-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s134/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Patent Applicant","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"An applicant for a patent, any of whose claims has been twice rejected, may appeal from the decision of the primary examiner to the Patent Trial and Appeal Board, having once paid the fee for such appeal.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idf3c19dbe-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s134/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Patent Owner","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"A patent owner in a reexamination may appeal from the final rejection of any claim by the primary examiner to the Patent Trial and Appeal Board, having once paid the fee for such appeal.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf3c19dbf-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-07-19/ch950"},"text":"July 19, 1952, ch. 950","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/801"},"text":"66 Stat. 801","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/622/tII/s204/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–622, title II, § 204(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-11-08"},"text":"Nov. 8, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/3388"},"text":"98 Stat. 3388","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4605/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4605(b)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–570; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/dC/tIII"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, div. C, title III","children":[],"tail":", §§ 13106(b), 13202(b)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1901"},"text":"116 Stat. 1901","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":", §§ 3(j)(1), (3), 7(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"},"text":"Sept. 16, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/290"},"text":"125 Stat. 290","children":[],"tail":", 313.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idf3c19dc0-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idf3c19dc1-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on Title 35, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 57 (R.S. 4909 amended (1) ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1927-03-02/ch273/s5"},"text":"Mar. 2, 1927, ch. 273, § 5","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/1335"},"text":"44 Stat. 1335","children":[],"tail":", 1336, (2) "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-08-05/ch451/s2"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1939, ch. 451, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/1212"},"text":"53 Stat. 1212","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Reference to reissues is omitted in view of the general provision in section 251. Minor changes in language are made.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idf3c19dc2-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf3c19dc3-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s3/j/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 3(j)(3)","children":[],"tail":", amended section catchline generally. Prior to amendment, section catchline read as follows: “Appeal to the Board of Patent Appeals and Interferences”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s3/j/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 3(j)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Patent Trial and Appeal Board” for “Board of Patent Appeals and Interferences”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s7/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 7(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “a reexamination” for “any reexamination proceeding”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s3/j/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 3(j)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Patent Trial and Appeal Board” for “Board of Patent Appeals and Interferences”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s7/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 7(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (c). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “A third-party requester in an inter partes proceeding may appeal to the Board of Patent Appeals and Interferences from the final decision of the primary examiner favorable to the patentability of any original or proposed amended or new claim of a patent, having once paid the fee for such appeal.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsecs. (a), (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s13202/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 13202(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “primary examiner” for “administrative patent judge”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s13202/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 13202(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “primary examiner” for “administrative patent judge”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s13106/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 13106(b)","children":[],"tail":", struck out at end “The third-party requester may not appeal the decision of the Board of Patent Appeals and Interferences.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113","children":[],"tail":" reenacted section catchline without change and amended text generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “An applicant for a patent, any of whose claims has been twice rejected, may appeal from the decision of the primary examiner to the Board of Patent Appeals and Interferences, having once paid the fee for such appeal.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/622"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–622","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Patent Appeals and Interferences” for “Appeals” in section catchline and text."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idf3c19dc4-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idf3c19dc5-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2011 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by section 3(j)(1), (3) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":" effective upon the expiration of the 18-month period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"},"text":"Sept. 16, 2011","children":[],"tail":", and applicable to certain applications for patent and any patents issuing thereon, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s3/n"},"text":"section 3(n) of Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date of 2011 Amendment; Savings Provisions note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s100"},"text":"section 100 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s7/b"},"text":"section 7(b) of Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":" effective upon the expiration of the 1-year period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"},"text":"Sept. 16, 2011","children":[],"tail":", and applicable to proceedings commenced on or after that effective date, with certain exceptions, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s7/e"},"text":"section 7(e) of Pub. L. 112